			<description><![CDATA[<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<strong>Neverware, Inc</strong> is looking for qualified, enthusiastic individuals to fill the critical role of system engineer in our Technical Operations Group.&nbsp; System engineers are responsible for the provisioning, assembly, installation, maintenance and support of all Neverware hardware and software at customer sites.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
The <strong>responsibilities</strong> of the systems engineer in Technical Operations will include, but not be limited to the following:</p>
<ul style="margin-left: 80px;">
<li>
Provisioning and assembly of all hardware to support Neverware services</li>
<li>
Install servers at new customer sites and properly configure all hardware, peripherals, services, settings, directories and storage</li>
<li>
Perform daily system monitoring of Neverware services at existing customer base.&nbsp; This includes:
<ul>
<li>
verifying the integrity and availability of all hardware, systems and key processes,</li>
<li>
reviewing system and application logs,</li>
<li>
and authenticating completion of scheduled jobs (i.e. backups, software updates)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
Provide technical support to all existing customers.&nbsp; This includes investigating and troubleshooting a wide range of issues, both remotely and on site.</li>
<li>
Development and delivery of product demonstrations</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
Applicants to this position should have the <strong>following qualifications</strong>:</p>
<ul style="margin-left: 80px;">
<li>
Basic proficiency in Linux system administration and basic network administration.&nbsp; (e.g. familiarity with the Linux command line)</li>
<li>
Comfortable with hardware installation, setup and networking</li>
<li>
Experience troubleshooting IT issues</li>
<li>
Comfortable interacting with end customers in person and via phone/email</li>
<li>
Basic exposure to shell scripting (BASH, python, ruby, perl)</li>
<li>
Certification or progress toward certification in relevant competencies (e.g. A+, CCNA, MCITP, etc)</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
